\newlabel{fig:cv_folds}{{8}{17}{Cross-validation partitioning scheme. The dataset is split into $K=5$ stratified folds: the first 250 samples of each training split are reserved for PCA fitting (left bracket), the remaining training examples are used for $\lambda $-optimisation (centre), and the held-out fold (green) serves as the final validation set}{figure.caption.13}{}}
